🛠 Engineering Challenges & Troubleshooting
During the development of our prototype, we encountered several technical hurdles. Below, we document our most significant challenge and how our team pivoted to a solution.

1. The LiDAR Reflectivity Crisis
The Problem:
Our initial navigation strategy relied heavily on LiDAR. While early bench testing (outside the chassis) showed excellent results, we encountered a critical failure during full-field integration: the laser signal absorption on black surfaces. The LiDAR pulses did not reflect reliably off the competition's black walls/elements, leading to significant mapping errors.

The Lesson Learned:
We fell into the trap of "isolated testing." By not testing the sensor in the final competition environment early enough, we overlooked environmental variables. This taught us the importance of system-level validation early in the design cycle.

The Solution:
With only 20 days remaining until the competition, we executed an emergency pivot:

Sensor Redesign: We transitioned from a single LiDAR system to a multi-point laser distance sensor array.

Rapid Prototyping: To integrate these new sensors, we designed and 3D-printed custom mounting brackets. This allowed us to iterate on the sensor angles and heights in hours rather than days.

Integration: This change required a complete overhaul of our navigation logic, which we managed through intensive coding sprints.

